ACT 682
* A person shall not be convicted of an offence under subsection (1) if it is proved that the offence was committed without that person's knowledge, and that care and due diligence was exercised to prevent the commission of the offence having regard to the circumstances.
* In furtherance of subsection (1), the Minister may make Regulations;
	* to prescribe guidelines for climatic requirement for sectoral activities;
	* for the establishment of meteorological stations;
	* for matters in respect of which fees are payable;
	* for the provision of aeronautical services;
	* to provide for uniform standards in the observation of meteorological phenomena;
	* generally for the achievement of the purposes of this Act.

disasters;
* refers to any level above ten metres from the surface of the earth;
